$AUDC The company's name is Audiocodes, I've posted a chart at the bottom but if you have a second, I'd love to know what you think of this company.

The Good:

So, they have phones in Walmart (fancy business IP phones) they are entwined with Microsoft Teams offering extensive communication products and services ranging from analytics to web cameras for Microsoft Teams and Zoom. They also are partnered with Cisco, Skype, and Google offering similar services. That's the broad view, the real narrative is their shift away from a hardware based phone company to a technology-software dominated communications company.

Since they've moved away from traditional IP phones (accelerated by the work at home norms) they've been able to generate a lot more more income specifically in UcaaS (Unified communications as a service) similar to the platform as a service, with UCaaS, unified communications services can be made available from the cloud to businesses from SMB to an enterprise. Bullish
